[size=4]Nested Dependencies[/size]

Some of the above mods have additional dependencies themselves, which you need to install as well. I will endeavour to keep the below list up-to-date, but you can always find all dependencies listed on the Thunderstore mod page for each mod.

[url=https://github.com/excellent-ae/zannc-GodsAPI/releases/latest]zannc-GodsAPI[/url]
[url=https://github.com/excellent-ae/zannc-KeepsakeExtender/releases/latest]zannc-KeepsakeExtender[/url]

I will not be providing troubleshooting support if the mod does not work due to missing dependencies or other issues resulting from a manual installation through Nexus Mods! Use r2modman for a one-click installation method.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/wkmLYM7.png[/img]

Note that the configuration file is only created after the first game start with the mod enabled in your mod manager.

If you are using r2modman or the Thunderstore Mod Manager, you can modify the config directly through the mod manager, in the "Config editor" tab.
Make sure to save the file once done.

You can find an explanation of all configuration options [url=https://github.com/NikkelM/Hades-II-HadesBiomes/wiki/Configuration]on this wiki page[/url].

